BVG India Plans $200 Million Ghana Sugar Project, Graphic Says

-- B y   M o s e s   M o z a r t   D z a w u
-- 
2011-05-18T11:54:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-18/bvg-india-plans-200-million-ghana-sugar-project-graphic-says.html
BVG India Ltd.  will invest $200
million to cultivate and process sugar cane in  Ghana , the Daily
Graphic reported, citing Managing Director H.R. Gaikwad.  The company will start with cultivation of 10,000 hectares
of the raw sweetener along the Volta Lake in eastern  Ghana , the
Accra-based newspaper cited Gaikwad as saying.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 